Noibu Issue #3552: PayPal/Braintree Buttons Fail To Initialize On Checkout

Description

Noibu Issue #3552 (demo.acme2.com) View in Noibu

Conversion impact: LIKELY Urgency: Med
First seen: April 11, 2025 Last seen: February 13, 2026

Problem

The checkout JavaScript throws a ReferenceError when it tries to read the braintree global, which stops the PayPal/Braintree initialization. As a result PayPal and PayPal Credit buttons may not appear or be usable on checkout pages. The failure is coming from the site's checkout JS file (main-checkout-hub.js).

Impact

The user-visible effect is that PayPal and PayPal Credit payment options may be missing or unresponsive on checkout pages (observed on checkout/hub pages). Customers can still often use other payment methods, but anyone trying to pay with PayPal/Braintree will not be able to start that flow. The problem appears frequently on mobile Safari/WebView environments, so a subset of customers (notably mobile users) are affected.

Technical details

Issue type: JavaScript
Error message: Cant find variable: braintree
Error signature: main-checkout-hub.js:cant find variable: braintree

The code checks braintree directly in this line: braintree && "undefined" != typeof paypal ? (console.debug("Paypal variables available"), f(a), clearInterval(b)) : console.debug("Waiting since braintree variable not available"). If the braintree global is not defined, referencing it raises Can't find variable: braintree instead of safely testing existence. This can happen because the thirdparty Braintree client SDK (which defines braintree) was not loaded yet, blocked, or missing, and the code used a direct variable access instead of a typeof existence check.
